== Chips ==

Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7 in a #oven{}.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{}, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

== Roasted Garlic ==

Meanwhile, pop the @garlic cloves{3}(unpeeled) into a small piece of #foil{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{} and scrunch to enclose it. Add the parcel to the chip baking tray and roast until soft, ~{10-12%minutes}.

== Pickled Onion Salad ==

Meanwhile, halve, peel and slice the @red onion{1/2}(peeled and sliced thinly) as thinly as you can.

Pop it into a large #bowl{} and add the @red wine vinegar{24%ml} and @sugar{1%tsp} for the pickle. Add a pinch of @salt{}, mix together and set aside to pickle.

== Tofu ==

Meanwhile, drain the @firm tofu{280%g} and thoroughly pat dry with #kitchen paper{}. Tear into 3cm chunks.

Add the tofu to a medium bowl with the @plain flour{1%tbsp} and the @roasted spice and herb blend{1%sachet}. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Heat a generous drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the tofu until slightly crispy, ~{8-10%minutes}. Turn frequently to ensure it doesn't burn.

== Roasted Garlic Tzatziki ==

While the tofu is cooking, trim the @baby cucumber{1}, then halve lengthways. Thinly slice widthways.

In a small bowl, combine the cucumber and @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g}. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, mix well and set aside.

Once the garlic has cooled, cut the end with #scissors{}, squeeze it out of the skin, and mash with a #fork{}. Stir through the cucumber yoghurt, then set your tzatziki aside.

== Assembly ==

Once the tofu is cooked, remove it from the heat. Add the @honey{15%g} and @smoky base paste{1%sachet} to the pan and turn to evenly coat.

> If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Add a splash of @water{} if it's a little too thick.

Pop the @Greek style flatbreads{2} (1 per person) into the oven until warm and starting to turn golden, ~{3-4%minutes}.

When everything's ready, share your flatbreads between your serving plates and spread over the @houmous{100%g}.

Top with the smoky sticky tofu, a spoonful of tzatziki and some of the pickled onions.

Toss the @baby leaf mix{20%g} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} through the remaining pickled onion to make your salad.

Serve your shish style flatbreads with the salad and chips alongside.

Enjoy!